<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_f4ff5c70-5c0c-4d33-8ca4-ff69503ad70c" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="SA"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/></meta><sptc>H5P3</sptc><title id="_dc776aa9-1379-463d-9f95-d51c4554842a">Access for inspection and maintenance</title><archive-num>2019: SA 6.1</archive-num><subclause id="_0c0a9edb-b1f5-46c4-9660-a104c11f6f7d" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_158f615c-e31f-4b6a-852e-4026235fe943">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>The space between buildings must be sufficient to allow access for inspection and maintenance to avoid hazardous conditions arising due to accumulation of rubbish that could—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_bc4542cc-7626-406c-b2ed-88604b49274d">bridge termite barriers; or</li><li id="_b53094c2-ecf4-4932-801c-362f1e89173f">harbour vermin; or</li><li id="_0df89ae5-0936-4a5e-88ae-8fa54ee0242c">create a fire hazard.</li></ol></subclause></clause>